.TH NGIT 1 "March 2026" "nmap-xyberpix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ngit \- scan GitHub repositories for common secret and password patterns
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ngit
.B \-\-authorized
.BI \-\-repo " OWNER/NAME"
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B ngit
.B \-\-authorized
.BI \-\-scan\-count " N"
.RB [ \-\-random ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ngit
clones each target repository with
.BR git (1)
.RB ( \-\-depth " 1)
and scans text files under the working tree with regular\-expression rules
(AWS\-style keys, GitHub tokens, private key blocks, common
.BR password = / api_key
assignments, Stripe keys, etc.). PEM
.B private
keys are always detected; PEM
.B public X.509 certificates
are optional (\fB\-\-include\-certificates\fR).
.PP
.B Important:
Use only on repositories you
.B own
or are
.B explicitly authorized
to assess. Indiscriminate scanning of third\-party repositories may violate law,
contract, and GitHub\(cqs terms of use.
.B ngit
refuses to run unless you pass
.B \-\-authorized
or set
.BR NGIT_AUTHORIZED=1 .
.PP
.B \-\-repo
scans one public repository.
.B \-\-scan\-count
uses the GitHub REST
.B search/repositories
API to discover repositories matching
.B \-\-search\-query
then scans up to
.I N
of them in repository order unless
.B \-\-random
is set, in which case repositories are drawn from random result pages (still
capped by GitHub\(cqs search limits).
.PP
Unauthenticated search is heavily rate\-limited; set
.B GITHUB_TOKEN
or
.B \-\-token
for a personal access token (or fine\-grained token with appropriate read scope).
.B git
must be installed for cloning.
.PP
Findings are written to standard output
.B immediately
as they are discovered (each block is flushed). Each match includes the GitHub
.I owner/repo
name, file path and line number, a rule
.BR type ,
and the matched
.B value
(redacted by default; use
.B \-\-show\-secrets
for full text; long values may be truncated). Multi\-line PEM blocks are one
finding each. Add
.B \-\-extra\-regex " LABEL=PATTERN"
for org\-specific rules (repeatable).
.B \-\-type
and
.B \-\-exclude\-type
filter by finding
.B type
(rule name or
.BR pem_ * label;
shell\-style globs via
.BR fnmatch (3)).
.B \-\-keyword
narrows secret/regex hits to lines containing a substring;
.B \-\-keyword\-scan
searches only for keywords (type
.BR keyword_hit ).
Heuristic rules produce false positives.
Regex matches per line and PEM blocks per file are capped to limit pathological
input cost (see fork
.B CHANGELOG
entries).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-authorized
Required acknowledgement (or
.BR NGIT_AUTHORIZED=1 ).
.TP
.BI \-\-repo " OWNER/NAME"
Single repository to scan.
.TP
.BI \-\-scan\-count " N"
Scan
.I N
repositories from search (mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-repo
as the primary mode; if both are given,
.B \-\-repo
wins and count is ignored).
.TP
.B \-\-random
Randomize which search result pages are used (with
.BR \-\-scan\-count ).
.TP
.BI \-\-search\-query " QUERY"
Query string for
.BR /search/repositories
(default:
.IR stars:>5 " pushed:>2024-01-01 ).
.TP
.BI \-\-token " TOKEN"
GitHub token (overrides
.B GITHUB_TOKEN
/ GH_TOKEN).
.TP
.BI \-\-seed " N"
Seed for random page selection.
.TP
.B \-\-insecure
Disable TLS certificate verification for GitHub HTTPS (API and
.BR git " clone).
For debugging only; prefer fixing the trust store (e.g.\&
.BI SSL_CERT_FILE
to a CA bundle such as Homebrew\(cqs
.I /opt/homebrew/etc/ca-certificates/cert.pem ,
or
.B pip " install certifi ).
.TP
.B \-\-show\-secrets
Print full matched values (default: redact/mask; unsafe for logs or shared
terminals).
.TP
.B \-\-include\-certificates
Also flag PEM
.B CERTIFICATE
blocks (public X.509), not only private keys and not CSR
.RB ( CERTIFICATE " REQUEST).
.TP
.BI \-\-extra\-regex " LABEL=PATTERN"
Extra line\-based rule; first
.B =
separates label (letters, digits, underscore; max 63 chars after first) from
the Python regex. Prefer one capturing group for the secret; otherwise the
whole match is shown (subject to
.BR \-\-show\-secrets ).
Repeat for multiple rules.
.TP
.BI \-\-type " GLOB"
Only emit findings whose
.B type
matches a
.BR fnmatch (3)
glob (e.g.\&
.IR aws* ", " pem_* ).
Repeat or use comma\-separated globs in one argument.
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude\-type " GLOB"
Skip types matching this glob (repeatable or comma\-separated). Applied after
.BR \-\-type .
.TP
.BI \-\-keyword " TEXT"
Normal scan: require this substring (case\-insensitive) on the line for regex
secret hits. Keyword scan: search for this text (repeatable).
.TP
.BI \-\-keyword\-file " PATH"
Extra keywords, one per line (
.B #
starts a comment). Merged with
.BR \-\-keyword .
Repeatable.
.TP
.B \-\-keyword\-scan
Clone and report lines matching any keyword only (finding type
.BR keyword_hit );
does not run built\-in secret regexes or PEM detection. Requires
.B \-\-keyword
and/or
.BR \-\-keyword\-file .
.TP
.B \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Progress and rate\-limit hints on standard error.
.TP
.BI \-\-siem\-log " PATH"
After a successful run, append one NDJSON line to
.I PATH
(event
.BR ngit_scan_summary ;
same
.B schema_version
style as Nmap
.BR \-\-siem\-log ).
Contains repository and finding
.B counts
only, never matched secret text.
.TP
.BI \-\-siem\-tag " TAG"
Optional string stored in the SIEM summary line (e.g. engagement label).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B ngit \-\-authorized \-\-repo OWNER/NAME \-\-type \(aqaws*\(aq
limits output to AWS\-related finding types;
.B ngit \-\-authorized \-\-repo OWNER/NAME \-\-keyword\-scan \-\-keyword password
reports lines containing that substring as
.BR keyword_hit " findings.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NGIT_AUTHORIZED
If set to
.BR 1 ,
equivalent to
.BR \-\-authorized .
.TP
.B GITHUB_TOKEN ", " GH_TOKEN
Default API and clone authentication for private repos the token can read.
.TP
.B SSL_CERT_FILE
If set to a PEM CA bundle path,
.B ngit
uses it for GitHub API TLS verification (helps Homebrew Python builds without a default bundle).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, 2 on usage or refusal to run, 1 if an unhandled error occurs.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git (1),
.BR nmap (1)
.SH AUTHORS
.B ngit
was added in the nmap\-xyberpix tree alongside Nmap.
